Breaking up in marriage is not acceptable, so the quality of marriages in Kosovo is rather questionable. However, the results of these researchers also disagree with empirical findings that divorce is more likely for couples with high expectations for marriage and for those experiencing financial stress.
The majority of men have had at least one partner in the previous six months and in contrast, the majority of women have not. The magnitude of difference is still recorded in relationships, marriage and with a family at rural homes, followed by migration in the sex division of labor and civil status.
Number of the children: The children are an important priority for the family. With respect to the marital status of the men and the number of children, the majority of married men are responsible for using contraception with females. There was a huge difference between the number of the children before and after marriage, taking into account the fact that in the previous 5 years, less than half of the children who were married were still married. A lot of women (from 44,9 to 47,3%), especially those who are married had experience with
the phenomenon of abortion compared to men in general, respectively to married men in particular, and were the cause of a child's birth, abortion or death as reported by (Gashi and colleagues, 2019).
